OL,3,CAncient ritual of blowing into shell
OL,4,C'could help with common sleep disorder'
OL,6,FAn ancient ritual which involves
OL,7,Fblowing into a large shell could
OL,8,Ftackle the symptoms of a common sleep
OL,9,Fdisorder, a study suggests.
OL,11,FThe practice of conch blowing, also
OL,12,Fknown as shankh blowing, could improve
OL,13,Fsleep for patients with obstructive
OL,14,Fsleep apnoea (OSA) without the need
OL,15,Ffor uncomfortable machinery, according
OL,16,Fto researchers.
OL,18,FShankh blowing involves breathing in
OL,19,Fdeeply before exhaling forcefully into
OL,20,Fa conch, the spiral-shaped shell from
OL,21,Fa species of sea snail.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
