OL,3,CAncient ritual of blowing into shell
OL,4,C'could help with common sleep disorder'
OL,6,FDr Krishna K Sharma, of the Eternal
OL,7,FHeart Care Centre and Research
OL,8,FInstitute in Jaipur, India, said: "The
OL,9,Fway the shankh is blown is quite
OL,10,Fdistinctive.
OL,12,F"It involves a deep inhalation
OL,13,Ffollowed by a forceful, sustained
OL,14,Fexhalation through tightly pursed lips.
OL,16,F"This action creates strong vibrations
OL,17,Fand airflow resistance, which likely
OL,18,Fstrengthens the muscles of the upper
OL,19,Fairway, including the throat and soft
OL,20,Fpalate, areas that often collapse
OL,21,Fduring sleep in people with OSA.
