OL,3,CAncient ritual of blowing into shell
OL,4,C'could help with common sleep disorder'
OL,6,F"The shankh's unique spiralling
OL,7,Fstructure may also contribute to
OL,8,Fspecific acoustic and mechanical
OL,9,Feffects that further stimulate and
OL,10,Ftone these muscles."
OL,12,FContinuous positive airway pressure
OL,13,F(Cpap) machines are the first line of
OL,14,Ftreatment for OSA.
OL,16,FThey involve patients wearing a mask
OL,17,Fthat blows pressurised air into the
OL,18,Fnose and throat while they sleep.
OL,20,FHowever, they can be uncomfortable.
