OL,3,CAncient ritual of blowing into shell
OL,4,C'could help with common sleep disorder'
OL,6,FReacting to the findings, Professor
OL,7,FSophia Schiza, head of the ERS group
OL,8,Fon sleep disordered breathing, based
OL,9,Fat the University of Crete, Greece,
OL,10,Fsaid: "We know that OSA patients have
OL,11,Fpoor quality of sleep, and higher
OL,12,Frisks of high blood pressure, strokes
OL,13,Fand heart disease.
OL,15,F"A proportion of patients experience
OL,16,Fsleepiness during the day.
OL,18,F"While Cpap and other treatments are
OL,19,Favailable based on careful diagnosis
OL,20,Fof disease severity, there is still
OL,21,Fneed for new treatments.
OL,26,@rD@GOUwD@AOUzD@AOU
